# ============================================================
# JOB CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: job
scope: job.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for job.

## policy_rules
Job policy constrains:
- who may create/assign job roles
- who may hold or act within jobs
- what job detail may be disclosed
- when job-based actions must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- assignment scope must be explicit
- authority scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public job summary
- holder-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical job detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow job assignment only for valid authority
- allow job action only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden role widening through job labels
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If job identity,
assignment basis,
authority scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the job path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- assignment policy is explicit
- authority policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
